public class ArbitrarilyDiscretizedFunction2D
extends DiscretizedFunction2D

Title: ArbitrarilyDiscretizedFunction2D
Description: This class allows any spacing betwee the x-points, i.e. there is no order to the spacing.

SWR: Note - not all funtionality has been implemented yet, such as all iterators except getPointsIterator().

Field Detail

dataPoints2D

protected DataPoint2DTreeMap dataPoints2D
The set of DataPoints2D that conprise the discretized function. These are stored in a DataPoint2D TreeMap so they are sorted on the X-Values
Constructor Detail

ArbitrarilyDiscretizedFunction2D

public ArbitrarilyDiscretizedFunction2D(java.util.Comparator comparator)
The passed in comparator must be an implementor of DataPoint2DComparatorAPI. These comparators know they are dealing with a DataPoint2D and usually only compare the x-values for sorting. Special comparators may wish to sort on both the x and y values, i.e. the data points are geographical locations.
